title: EAlarmStorageReaderErrors (Enum)
text:
TYPE EAlarmStorageReaderErrors :
This enumeration defines the errors, that can occur during accessing the alarm
storage using the public interface.
Note: Error codes from 30400 to 30549 represent errors from the underlying
CAA Storage component. See STO.ERROR
Attributes:
qualified_only

rows.Name: WrongParameter
rows.Comment:
A required parameter is invalid, e.g. NULL is passed, where
an instance is required

rows.Name: NoMemory
rows.Comment:
Unable to allocate an internally used buffer resp. unable to
store a value

rows.Name: NoObject
rows.Comment: The specified object was not found

rows.Name: AdditionalReadCallRequired
rows.Comment:
This is not really an error, but the information, that all the data cannot be read
by a single call and additional method calls are necessary

rows.Name: InvalidCall
rows.Comment:
The call to a method is invalid, because this method cannot
be called in this context.
